The paper deals with a game-theoretic problem of revenue maximization in online auctions, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves learning the distribution of private values over time, which suggests a connection to online learning (cs.LG) and reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The use of reserve prices and the second price auction mechanism also suggests a connection to mechanism design (cs.GT). The paper involves analyzing regret bounds, which suggests a connection to optimization and control (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
